      <div class="basics">
        <h1>The Basics</h1>
        <p>
A security incident is a violation or imminent threat of violation of computer security policies, acceptable use policies, or standard security practices. While preventive activities based on the results of risk assessments can lower the number of incidents, not all incidents can be prevented. You need an incident response capability to detect incidents quickly, minimize loss and destruction, mitigate exploited system weaknesses, and restore IT services.
        </p>
